                            <comment id="253396" author="stancheff" created="Wed, 21 Aug 2019 14:35:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As Patrick pointed out this issue doesn&apos;t exist master since &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10070&quot; title=&quot;PFL self-extending file layout&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10070&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-10070&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="253395" author="stancheff" created="Wed, 21 Aug 2019 14:33:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Okay I&apos;ll run through my test again ... and it looks like it works fine on master so this patch isn&apos;t needed. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="253391" author="pfarrell" created="Wed, 21 Aug 2019 14:22:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Shaun,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Pools created by tests are now cleaned up automatically, at least if they use TESTNAME (and I think maybe all of them, ie, regardless of name?) for the pool, like test_253 does.&#160; That functionality (take a look at create_pool - it adds a stack_trap for destroy_test_pools) hasn&apos;t been around forever, so some tests still remove their own pool, but it is not actually necessary any more.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
